sentences.content: I tell [my stroke story](mystrokevc,page) since my aphasia using this reading companion.
I describe who I was and who I am since my severe hemorrhagic stroke in 2015.
The speech recognition feature allows me to practice by myself.
Introduce myself and tell my story.
I use this when I introduce myself to others.
I will be able to introduce myself better as I practice more.
I can practice introducing myself everyday.
I use [my strategies](mystrategies,page) to help me recover from aphasia caused by my severe hemorrhagic stroke in 2015.
The speech recognition feature allows me to practice by myself.
Use these strategies in my everyday life to I overcome aphasia.
I use these strategies to help overcome aphasia.
These strategies were developed by my Speech and Language Pathologists.
I can use these strategies everyday.
I can practice remembering these strategies every week.
I use these exercises to practice my word finding.
Improve my word finding for nouns, verbs and other parts of speech.
I can improve word finding given specific context and possible responses.
I can practice my word finding everyday.
These exercises allow me to fill in sentences progressively.
Improve my sentence formation by understanding the underlying syntax rules and patterns.
parts of speech and sentence structure.
the sentence tenses (like past present, future), syntax rules and patterns (like arrangement, order).
I can improve my sentence formation by relearning the rules by which sentences are constructed.
I can practice my sentence formation everyday
I can practice retrieving action words on flashcards.
I want to improve my ability to recall verbs and including helping and linking verbs until I overcome aphasia.
I use these fillin exercises to practice recalling action words based on flashcard pictures until I say them.
I can practice these flashcard fillins each week.
This book club is reading Shadow Divers and is hosted by Voices of Hope for Aphasia for Spring 2024.
This book club is reading Lessons In Chemistry and is hosted by Aphasia Treatment Program for Winter 2024.
This book club is reading I Must Betray You and is hosted by Boston University for Winter 2024.
This book club is reading Remarkably Bright Creatures and is hosted by Speech Recovery Pathways for Winter 2024.
These are past book club summaries.
Scene narratives the user describe complex scenes in a structured approach with numeric labels.
I use these narrative fillin exercises to practice describing complex scenes in a structured approach with numeric labels.
I can practice these narratives each week.
A man goes to the hair salon.
Another man is already in the waiting room
The hair designer is cutting a woman's hair
I can practice reading sentences of different lengths.
I can review my recent experiences and practice recounting my current events by looking at photos and captions.
